**Current Implementation:**
Some good language but not systematically enforced translation.

**What Needs Addition:**

#### **Create Explicit "Never Say / Always Say" Reference:**

**Add New Reference Section: "Language Translation Table"**

| ❌ NEVER Use | ✅ ALWAYS Use |
|-------------|--------------|
| Cold email | Private infrastructure for channel deployment |
| Email software/tool | Proprietary systems |
| List building | Market research / data acquisition |
| Copywriting | Campaign design with enterprise pedigree |
| Outreach campaign | Diligence-backed demand generation |
| Email sequence | Nurture architecture |
| Lead generation | Qualified opportunity creation |
| Spam check | Deliverability optimization |
| Open rates | Engagement metrics |
| Click rates | Interest signals |

**Strategic Deflection Pattern:**
```
"Until we can put together the engagement model, which allows us to see 
the end of the engagement before we even begin, I wouldn't be able to 
tell you exact tactics or give you a detailed breakdown of how we'd 
execute month-by-month."
```

**Why This Matters:**
- Systematic vocabulary replacement (not ad hoc)
- "Operators explain. Advisors orchestrate."
- Mechanism protection (mystery = value)
- Thesis document treats language precision as frame protection

**Implementation Impact:** ⭐⭐⭐⭐ HIGH PRIORITY

